ow these recorded performances provided Jewish immigrants from Europe with a venue for lamenting the decline of their home communities and for connecting their memories to the present. Analyzing sonic material against the backdrop of its artistic, cultural, and ideological contexts, Abeliovich develops a critical framework for the study of sound as a discipline in its own right in theater scholarship.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 0aJewish theater. 0aTheaterzIsrael. 4aJewish Studies : Jewish Studies. 4aLiterature : Drama. 4aLiterature : Hebrew Language and Literature. 4aLiterature : Literary Criticism. 4aLiterature : Literature. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Theater / History & Criticism.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package 2019z978311149143140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438474458423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438474458/original  a978-3-11-149143-1  SUNY Press eBook Package 2019b2019  aGBV-deGruyter-alles